w york’s gotham hall on october th  smulyan will be among an elite group of industry professionals who will be recognized for their contributions to  the media during the course of the last halfcentury jeffrey smulyan who serves as chairman of the board of emmis communications corporation an indianapolis–based radio tv and magazine publishing company with operations in  us markets and slovakia and bulgaria will be joining  giants of broadcasting who have been honored by the library since the awards were instigated in    jeff smulyan graduated cum laude from the university of southern california with a ba in history and telecommunications going on to earn a juris doctor degree from usc school of law during which time he served as note and comment editor of the school’s law review after operating two radio stations – wnts in indianapolis and kcro in omaha jeff smulyan founded emmis in   taking it public  in  currently emmis owns and operates  fm and  am radio stations in the united states as well as radio stations in slovakia and bulgaria in  emmis earned the distinction of becoming the first company to own toprated stations in new york and los angeles simultaneously over the past two decades smulyan has been named among the most influential people in the radio industry in addition to his business activities smulyan was named by the white house to head the us delegation to the plenipotentiary conference of the international telecommunications union in  acting as the united states ambassador he represented the his country in a series of history shaping a series bilateral agreements particularly one between israel and the plo jeff smulyan sits on the board of trustees of the university of southern california as well as being a member of numerous civic boards and committees in the city of indianapolis and the state of indiana other honors that smulyan has won include the cystic fibrosis foundation’s breath of life award the jewish national fund’s tree of life award the leukemia society diamond of hope award as well as being inducted into the indiana business hall of fame in  the broadcasters’ foundation honored smulyan with its golden mike award in recognition of his charitable efforts jeff smulyan is also recognized as being a considerate employer with emmis being named one of fortune magazine’s “ best companies to work for”on more than one occasion in recent years smulyan has been recognized as being among the principal innovators in the radio industry’s groundbreaking efforts to expand the reach of fm radio to a mobile platform   read more about cystic fibrosis foundations breath of life award emmis communications corporation fortune magazine giants of broadcasting gotham hall indiana business hall of fame jeff smulyan jeffry smullian jewish national funds tree of life award library of american broadcasting plenipotentiary conference of the international telecommunications union the broadcasters’ foundation the white house about the author stanley green  related news  comments nbsp get livefyre faq sign in  follow post comment   link newest  oldest most popular tags technology ceo business united states israeli new york jewish businessfinance people israel all rights reserved  terms  conditions  privacy policy  sitemap contact  subscribe  comment email delivered by feedburner jeffrey h smulyan joins usc board of trustees  usc news skip to menu skip to content university of southern california usc news menu search search menu search subscribe to receive usc news via email subscribe jeffrey h smulyan joins usc board of trustees by gilien silsby january   jeffrey h smulyan a usc alumnus and chairman of emmis communications corp has been elected to the board of trustees photo by tony valanis jeffrey h smulyan chairman president and principal shareholder of emmis communications corp an indianapolisbased broadcasting company has been elected to the usc board of trustees smulyan is a presidential associate and a member of the board of councilors of the usc annenberg school for communication and the usc law school he is past regional director of usc’s midwest alumni club and past president of the indianapolis alumni club he earned both his bachelor’s degree and a law degree from usc in announcing smulyan’s election usc president steven b sample said “jeff smulyan is a dedicated and energetic addition to our board of trustees as an alumnus who served as class president in his senior year on campus he has a deep commitment to this university and its mission we look forward to his leadership” smulyan founded emmis communications corp in  today the company – which went public in  – boasts  million in annual sales it owns and operates  radio stations in the nation’s largest markets including new york city los angeles kzla and kpwr – “power ” and chicago it also operates  television stations in cities stretching from orlando to honolulu emmis also owns and operates six city and regional magazines including los angeles texas monthly and atlanta last year smulyan received the national association of broadcasters’ national radio award and as radio ink’s “radio executive of the year” “it is a great honor to be elected to the usc board of trustees” smulyan said “i have such fond memories of the university from both my undergraduate and law school days as a current usc parent i have been very excited about the remarkable achievements that the university has made under dr sample it is with much pride that i accept this” after earning his jd degree from usc law school in  smulyan entered the radio business operating two stations in indianapolis and omaha before forming emmis as principal shareholder of emmis smulyan led a group to purchase the seattle mariners baseball team in  he sold the club three years later smulyan a former director of the national association of broadcasters and former chairman of the board of directors of the radio advertising bureau serves as chair of the central indiana corporate partnership a consortium of ceos from the largest central indiana corporations smulyan also sits on the board of trustees of ball state university and the board of directors of finish line inc an athletic apparel company he is a member of the american indiana and federal communications bar associations and has served on numerous civic boards and committees in  he was named by the white house as us ambassador to head the delegation to the plenipotentiary conference of the international telecommunications union a cum laude graduate of usc smulyan earned a ba in history and telecommunications in  smulyan enjoys sports politics and reading he lives in indianapolis and has two children bradley  and cari  a senior majoring in theater at usc jeffrey h smulyan joins usc board of trustees top stories on usc news university usc village with the los angeles skyline in the background is seen in this image from an overhead drone photocourtesy of usc capital construction development drone video fences are coming down and usc village is almost ready for its debutshops and restaurants are coming together and the first of  student residents arrive at the  million development in less than four weeks health a new report says that one in three cases of dementia could be prevented by decreasing risk factors such as poor childhood education hypertension and obesity and smoking later in life photoistock experts  in  cases of dementia preventablelancet commission including usc expert has identified powerful tools to prevent dementia and touts the benefits of nonmedical interventions humanities the gaelic language and its impact on culture and identity was the focus of usc students during their trip to ireland photomartijn van exel immersed in irish culture students learn why gaelic language languisheshalf the world’s languages could disappear in a few decades and usc dornsife’s tok thompson is helping students figure out why — and what might be lost subscribe to receive usc news via email subsc